translate ru TheOldRoad6_95fc50df:
    # "When they departed from the crossroads, they left behind the last of any real threats."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_02052c3b:
    # "Before long, just as Sigmund predicted, the roads turned safer as they drew closer to Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_dc2f0dae:
    # "In the last few days, neither Sarah nor Sakar wasted what little time they had guaranteed."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_7b4e1466:
    # "Each night she spend with him."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_044c1fc9:
    # "Sakar was more experienced than her, but Sarah was a fast and eager student."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_660cca9d:
    # "Hiding and sneaking around was pointless and soon abandoned. By the end, Sarah and Sakar vanished into the bushes with few doubts as to their intentions."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_7f2a4a45:
    # "She saw Sigmund disaproved of her, but she didn't care much for his approval or disapproval anymore. He was not the father-figure he pretended to be."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_6ffdb40c:
    # "And so, with little sleep and a great deal of exhaustion from their frequent encounters, Sarah found herself sore and tired."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_d56d3f20:
    # "It was in that condition, seated up front on the wagon, when her eyes first fell upon the city of Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_95fc50df_1:
    # "When they departed from the crossroads, they left behind the last of any real threats."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_02052c3b_1:
    # "Before long, just as Sigmund predicted, the roads turned safer as they drew closer to Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5a9ff229:
    # "The roads grew busier and busier."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5efda052:
    # "Before long, they were just one of many trade carts."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_b366a93e:
    # "After several days of travelling in what now seemed an unfamiliar sense of safety, that Sarah's eyes first fell upon the city of Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_67707d25:
    # "Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f2222eef:
    # "The capital of the Mythran empire."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_b20b9db2:
    # "In all the world, there were no cities that could make a claim to be its rival."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_a49a23c8:
    # "The empire that it represented, likewise, possessed no equal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_0e0f0176:
    # "The landmass that now fell under this singular dominion was once a collection of fueding nations, not all that different from the union kingdoms that Sarah hailed from."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f0260c32:
    # "Flanked on one side by the central kingdoms, equal in power but more unified, and flanked on the other side by the Hyral mountains, the open and vast plains made its land vulnerable from all sides."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_c9c96fd8:
    # "For centuries, this was the fate of this corner of the world, to be looted by its neighbours, both human and orc."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_b6afffd0:
    # "Its large and fertile fields lured in endless throngs of fortune seekers. But the land was nearly impossible to defend by virtue of its geography."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f8dbec4c:
    # "Those brave enough to try would settle. Prosper. And like a pig grown fat, slaughtered and eaten by a rival."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_7cd92dc1:
    # "Those fortunate were enslaved by humans. Those less fortunate by the orcs."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_10c34db6:
    # "On and on, the land proved a temptation that could not be resisted by those seeking better fortunes, only to betray them or their descendants in time."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_37ae00f2:
    # "The land itself was a trap."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_04413a48:
    # "This cycle continued without fail for centures, to the point some even imagined it cursed."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_c8029e92:
    # "But it was finally the nation of Mythra, that broke the cycle."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_bd164ae9:
    # "Before it was a nation, it was the city of Rahayal only."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_accc1e90:
    # "But the location of the city's founding made it uniquely defensible in a land otherwise vulnerable."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_4e6939fe:
    # "From this position of strength, the city grew and grew."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_03dad41e:
    # "This was not the first time a city had prospered for longer than usual, and so many still speculated on its inevitable defeat at the hands of man or orc."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_fbc54e0a:
    # "But the defeat never came."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_832e60be:
    # "As the city of Rahayal grew and grew, it was rather its neighbours that found themselves declining."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_61bed24f:
    # "The central kingdoms saw the rise of the city, and understood it to be a possible rival. But each time they sought to put down this new rival, they fell into infighting."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_4ba221d2:
    # "The orc warlords saw in Rahayal a fat prize, bearing hundreds-of-thousands potential slaves and mountains of gold."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_48534c18:
    # "But each time an orc chieftain tried to rally his horde, another clan declared a rivalry, or one was assassinated."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_57f5015e:
    # "So, round and round, the enemies of Rahayal found themselves perpetually distracted."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_a5b3f6da:
    # "Distracted, until one day they realized that their potential rival had grown into a real one."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5ef90ab2:
    # "By now, Rahayal had grown strong and powerful off the rich lands. Its endless fields of grain fed the mouths of millions, sustaining a population large than any that part of the world has seen."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5388ce52:
    # "When the enemies of Rahayal finally showed up to their gates, they found not pallisades but walls carved from stone and steel."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_53f291eb:
    # "The central kingdoms were the first to break themselves up their walls."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_e4a6e520:
    # "The orc hordes, finally broken from their own civil war, flowed out from their mountains into the open fields, hungry for conquest."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_ef46582c:
    # "But they were met out on the open fields, and their raw strength proved no match for the modern warfare of the Mythran armies."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_c314e55c:
    # "The first legion of the Mythra broke the orcish horde in open battle, driving them back into the mountains."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_b05ddf86:
    # "And so, the enemies of Rahayal, dared not to try again."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_4e3a8e32:
    # "In turn, the city surged outwards."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_1170cec9:
    # "Theirs was only the hand of violence. For as many neighbours as they conquered, so many they bribed, or annexed through trade."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_b2ffcf7b:
    # "In less than a century, every other power in the region had fallen under the sway of what was now officially the Mythran empire."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f3297568:
    # "Its endless fields. Its countless mines. Its unrivaled industry."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5fa74d6d:
    # "Mythra became the region's superpower."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_ac0a5667:
    # "The central kingdoms fell to infighting, too disunited to pose any opposition."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_94f20165:
    # "The orcish horde, humiliated by their defeat, saw an endless conflict between clans and chieftains."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_2c6ab4eb:
    # "Only small orc bands ever dared to leave their mountains again."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_37547395:
    # "Over time, they turned inward, obsessed only with fighting on another, and leaving the human world to its own designs."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_6b416633:
    # "So it came to be that the city of Rahayal grew into the empire of Mythra."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_395e04b8:
    # "Its capital, the crowning jewel of its empire."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_ee096f45:
    # "The city was largely carved out of marble, giving it the appearance in daylight of almost glowing, as though it was as blessed as it pretended to be."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_a0c38682:
    # "The only object that defied its otherwise uniform design, was the pyramid of Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_a3dc8100:
    # "A void-like structure, carved out of some metal or stone that existed nowhere else in the world."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_cc8d4125:
    # "Nobody knew or could tell if the pyramid had been build in the city, or if the city had been build around the pyramid."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f77a9be0:
    # "The thing sat upon the city like a scar, dominating it, no matter from where one looked upon it."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_0aa60c0f:
    # "To strangers and visitors, the thing was impossible to ignore. To those who lived in the city, the thing was almost impossible to notice."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_ef9a4b2c:
    # "Those most at home to the city conceived of the structure as though it was a beggar in the streets. Consciously noticed, consciously ignored."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_39d2df2e:
    # "Sarah too, could not ignore the thing."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_d6c88970:
    # s "What is that?"
    s ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5acef3aa:
    # "She pointed towards the structure that seemed to eat the light around it."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_44b014b9:
    # sig "That's the pyramid of Rahayal."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_4eddce9c:
    # sig "That's where the Noctori live."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_96df6c59:
    # s "Noctori?"
    s ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_94d281eb:
    # "Sigmund looked at her."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_34bdfb01:
    # sig "You can read and write, you're educated enough, and you're telling me you don't know about them?"
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_4d4cd095:
    # "Sarah shook her head."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_cbbec679:
    # sig "Did they never bother to teach you any history?"
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_ee4c812c:
    # "They had, quite a lot of it in fact. But most it had revolved around the union kingdoms and Rosanna itself."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_fb68826f:
    # "Sarah had come to realize she really didn't know all that much about this side of the ocean."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_60082ccd:
    # s "Not about this place, no."
    s ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_c9cad8a1:
    # sig "Well, the Noctori are the ruling class of the Mythran empire, and that pyramid is where they hold court."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_94ec93a7:
    # sig "The eternal court, they call it."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_8634ccda:
    # s "The eternal court?"
    s ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_68fe79dc:
    # "Sigmund spat next to the wagon."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_9960669c:
    # sig "Arrogant shit for arrogant folks. Nothin lasts forever, not even this place. But I guess they call it that, hopin to make it true."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_d7d898c0:
    # "Sarah looked back at the imposing structure."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_c2c7d4f7:
    # "She tried to think of the thing like a castle, the seat of power, just as her home of Castle Reinmeer had been."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_1f01cd8c:
    # "Still, she struggled."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_0e0955e2:
    # "The object looked too alien. Reinmeer had been a place full of warmth and life. This thing seemed devoid of either."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_92cc815d:
    # "Unwilling to spend much more thought on the structure, Sarah allowed her eyes to drift across the rest of Rahayal."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_926d3f42:
    # "Almost instantly, she felt her soul soothed."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_e1191c57:
    # "Where the pyramid was a construct of darkness, the city was one of light."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_1001562a:
    # "Its ocean of marble and white stone reflected the rising sun, basking all of it in a glow that made Sarah feel safe and warm."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f05a985d:
    # "A home, she thought. That's what it reminded her of."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_b8e4cd61:
    # "The more she looked at the rest of the city, the easier she found it to ignore the haunting pyramid."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_1c1c60df:
    # "After a while, they finally came upon the gates of the city."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f0f34b04:
    # "The gates to the city were wide open and the city guards seemed amicable enough, standing only half-serious at their post."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_9e380b3f:
    # "Flowing into and out of the city was a near endless stream of caravans and wagons."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_cb7c1ae4:
    # "Sarah had never seen an economy of this scale."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_a41db29a:
    # "Where on the old road they had often been alone, they were now one of a great many."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_d217c56a:
    # "Hardly anybody gave them a glance."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_c7d514f2:
    # sig "Well, I suppose we've reached the end of our road."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_ad59a496:
    # "Sigmund held out a bag."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_a42d879d:
    # "Sarah took it from him, feeling the weight of it, she knew it was a fair bit of money."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_5956d4f9:
    # s "Thank you, Sigmund. I really don't know what else to say."
    s ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_f6a95a1f:
    # sig "Don't say nothing, child. You want to thank me? Just take good care of yourself, that's all I want for you."
    sig ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_e220fdaf:
    # "Sarah smiled and nodded."
    ""

translate ru TheOldRoad6_96281a14:
    # s "I will, I promise."
    s ""

